a-size-base 3: I give one of these to my young puppy every night at bedtime.  Takes him just a couple of minutes to chew, but settles him right down and he knows it is part of the routine. There are puppy teething rings made by this same company which last a bit longer - but they also cost more and you don't get very many in a package.  I use those when I have them for the same purpose of settling my puppy down at bedtime, but they also don't do much to satisfy the need to chew, despite the name of the product. a-size-base 2: Reviewed in the United States on January 9, 2017
a-size-base 3: I absolutely love these and so do the pups! Many people also use them as a treat as they do get eaten very quickly and some would argue that they do not help for teething. I have two King Charles Cavaliers and used these for both when they were puppies and I also used them for the litter of pups we just had. For a small breed dogs and young pups these do work great for teething. I gave them to the pups when they started getting teeth and they were unable to "eat" them yet but they loved the taste and it did help them with teething. Once they got older and were able to eat them it was more of a reward yes but it still helped with their back teeth which take the longest time to "pop out". The momma and daddy dogs even tried to steal them because they are so yummy! I also like these because they are edible and are much healthier to eat then raw hides. I recommended these to all of the new owners of our pups!
